Investment Philosophy
Opus Investment Management's investment
    philosophy is embodied in three principles:

Yield wins over time. Continued
        investment in higher-yielding bonds has historically provided investors
        with attractive risk-adjusted returns. 
Inefficiencies in fixed income markets present return opportunities.
      Periodic lapses in information flows, a lack of standardized
        option pricing and the rapid development
        of new and increasingly complex structured
        products cause inefficiencies in fixed income
        markets. 
A fundamental, research-driven
        approach allows us to identify under- and over-valued
        sectors and securities. Fundamental research is
        the key to capturing market inefficiencies. 

The Opus Investment Management Investment Strategy
      Group, comprised of our entire team of portfolio managers and research analysts, combines economic and
      fundamental financial analysis to determine on-going
      investment strategy.







